sentences: Filipe Melo (born 13 September 1977) is a Portuguese musician, film director and comic book writer.
In 2018, he directed "Sleepwalk", a short film based on one of his short stories.
In 2012 he was invited to write a story for the Eisner award-winning anthology Dark Horse Presents, also featuring works by Frank Miller and Mike Mignola.
His latest book, “Ballad for Sophie” was published by Top Shelf / IDW in 2021.
